d Kingdom","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"about 1290–":"omkring 1290–Afdød","1285–Female":"1285–Afdød","1305–1357":"1305–1357","1290–Male":"1290–Afdød","1305":"1305","1357":"1357","about 1290":"omkring 1290","October 1305":"oktober 1305","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1290–":"circa 1290–Overleden","1285–Female":"1285–Overleden","1305–1357":"1305–1357","1290–Male":"1290–Overleden","1305":"1305","1357":"1357","about 1290":"circa 1290","October 1305":"oktober 1305","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1290–":"about 1290–Deceased","1285–Female":"1285–Deceased","1305–1357":"1305–1357","1290–Male":"1290–Deceased","1305":"1305","1357":"1357","about 1290":"about 1290","October 1305":"October 1305","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hillary","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Caitlin, Ciaran.","English (of Norman origin):","from the Middle English and Old French male or female personal name <i>Hilari(e)</i>, <i>Ilari(e)</i>, and <i>Elari(e)</i>, from Latin <i>Hilarius</i> and <i>Hilaria</i> ‘joyful’ (from Greek <i>hilaros</i>). The Latin name was chosen by many early Christians to express their joy and hope of salvation, and was borne by several saints, including a 4th-century bishop of Poitiers (died 368) noted for his vigorous resistance to the Arian heresy, and a 5th-century bishop of Arles. Largely due to veneration of Saint Hilarius of Poitiers, the name became popular in France in the forms <i>Hilari</i> and <i>Hilaire</i>, and was brought to England by the Norman conquerors. Although quite popular in France, it was only occasionally used in England, where it was confused with the name in 2 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellery","meanings":["variant of   Hillary  .","habitational name from Elleray in Windermere (Westmorland), probably from Old Norse <i>elri</i> ‘alder’ + <i>vrá</i> ‘nook’.","English:"]},{"name":"Gloor","meanings":["Swiss German: from a vernacular form of the Latin personal name <i>Hilarius</i> (see   Hillary  )."]},{"name":"Hillier","meanings":["English (Wiltshire and Surrey): occupational name for a roofer from Middle English <i>hil(l)ier</i>, <i>hul(li)er</i>, <i>hel(li)er</i> ‘roofer, slater, tiler’, agent nouns from the Middle English verb <i>hil(i)en</i>, <i>hel(i)an</i>, <i>hul(i)en</i> ‘to put a roof on; cover with a roof’.","French: from the personal name <i>Hillier</i>, a vernacular form of <i>Hilaire</i> (see   Hillary  )."]},{"name":"Alario","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Orazio, Carlo, Rocco, Salvatore, Vita, Vitina.","Italian: from a vernacular form of the personal name <i>Ilario</i>, from Latin <i>Hilarius</i> (see   Hillary  ).","Italian (Sicily): probably a status name from dialect <i>alariu</i> ‘herald’."]},{"name":"Glor","meanings":["German: from a vernacular form of the Latin personal name <i>Hilarius</i> (see   Hillary  )."]},{"name":"Hillery","meanings":["English: variant of   Hillary  . This name has long been established in Ireland (Clare)."]},{"name":"Hilaire","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Pierre, Antoine, Chantal, Edeline, Georges, Luc, Maryse, Mimose, Serge, Yolaine.","French and West Indian (mainly Haiti): from the personal name <i>Hilaire</i>, French form of   Hillary   1. This surname is most common in Haiti. Compare   Helaire  ."]},{"name":"Hilleary","meanings":["English (Essex): variant of   Hillary  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Allaire","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Andre, Lucien, Alphonse, Antoine, Armand, Emile, Michel, Pierre, Raoul, Raymonde, Rolande.","French: from the Old French personal name <i>Allaire</i>, a variant of <i>Hilaire</i> (see   Hillary  ). Compare   Dallaire  .","History: Jean and Charles Allaire, two brothers from the Poitou region of France, are recorded in Quebec City, QC, in 1662 and 1663, respectively, the years of their marriage. The descendants of one or another brother also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Dallaire</i>, <i>Delair</i>, and <i>Delaire</i>. — Alexandre Allaire, a Huguenot refugee, brought the name from La Rochelle in France to New Rochelle, NY, in 1686, via the West Indies. He is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Hilario","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Julio, Alfredo, Luis, Abelardo, Arturo, Eduardo, Francisco, Juan, Mario, Pedro, Carlos, Cesar.  Portuguese Afonso, Joao.","Portuguese (<b>Hilário</b>) and Spanish: from a personal name ofthe same origin as   Hillary   1."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Hillary was born about 1290, in Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Agnes. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1290–":"umbes 1290–Surnud","1285–Female":"1285–Surnud","1305–1357":"1305–1357","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1305":"1305","1357":"1357","about 1290":"umbes 1290","October 1305":"oktoober 1305","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1290–":"noin 1290–Kuollut","1285–Female":"1285–Kuollut","1305–1357":"1305–1357","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1357":"1357","about 1290":"noin 1290","October 1305":"lokakuu 1305","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1290–":"environ 1290–Décédé","1285–Female":"1285–Décédée","1305–1357":"1305–1357","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1305":"1305","1357":"1357","about 1290":"environ 1290","October 1305":"octobre 1305","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","Bescot, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bescote, Staffordshire, England":"Bescot, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSumm